<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Alikat Astrae</div><div class="date">April 23rd, 2012, 09:47 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">Which is why you don't claim to have won any single pot or jackpot in excess of $600, but instead just won steadily at small bids and small jackpots.  You simply enter the income on your Schedule C and declare it as gambling winnings.  The 1099 is just to catch you if you DON'T declare it such a win.  You just declare your aggregate gambling winnings on a single line, there is no breakdown for individual wins.</div></div><hr />


