<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Branaman Starbinder</div><div class="date">April 25th, 2012, 09:48 AM</div></div><div class="posttext">If you go for Cash and storage, make sure you bury Platium or Gold or Silver (in that order) instead of some federal reserve IOU pieces of paper that can be declared worthless whenever the corporate climate of that private institution shifts.<br />
<br />
If you go for complete bankruptcy and get placed under curatorship /a Ward, make sure you have yourself a place to stay/rent first where you are comfortable. And make sure you have signed some long term rental/subscription contracts on (luxury) utilities like TV, Internet, newspaper and magazines you might need the next 5 years you will have no private income and will be paying off debts. They can not easily take away obligations you can defend, but they can easily deny you getting new ones.</div></div><hr />


